{
  "texts": [
    "During our Miller simulation, glycine is formed three times and persists for approximately 225 fs, 375 fs and 913 fs.",
    "Dissociation of glycine in less than 1 ps is expected, considering the relatively high temperature of this simulation.",
    "The final step to form glycine is hydrogen addition to C 2 H 4 NO 2, similar to the mechanism of Saitta and Saija.",
    "However, hydrogen addition occurs at an oxygen atom in our mechanism, rather than at the α-carbon as in the Saitta and Saija mechanism.",
    "In one instance, our Miller simulation produced the same C 2 H 4 NO 2 isomer as reported by Saitta and Saija."
  ]
}